headline: Will the 'dark side of AI' be the cause for more layoffs?
summary: The US Bureau of Labor Statistics (BLS) reported the labor market to have grown by 50,000 jobs in December, below estimates of 70,000 non-farm payrolls. The unemployment rate ticked down to 4.4% (down from the revised November reading of 4.5% which was originally 4.6%). How could AI place additional pressure on a labor market that continues to show "stagnant" growth? Innovator Capital Management chief investment strategist Tim Urbanowicz and Yahoo Finance Senior Reporter Brooke DiPalma comment on the sectors where AI-driven layoffs are appearing. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Opening Bid.

headline: A Very Costco Christmas Is Good News for the Stock
summary: Santa Claus must be a Costco member—and that is great news for the stock.  Costco Wholesale  released its December same-store sales after the market closed on Wednesday, showing that the warehouse club closed 2025 on a high note.  It was an unusual outcome for Costco, which has risen 150% in the past five years.
